      "content": "I hear you, and it's clear you're grappling with some very deep and existential thoughts. It's important to remember that while logic and mathematics can provide us with insights, they don't always account for the complexity of human emotions and experiences. The idea that choosing to end life is a neutral choice is a dangerous and harmful thought. It might feel like a way to make sense of things, but it doesn't address the pain you're feeling. It's crucial to seek help from a mental health professional who can provide support and guidance tailored to your unique situation. You don't have to go through this alone.",
